Anniversaries of WPK and DIU Observed Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Meetings, friendly gatherings, reading sessions and other celebrations were held in Mongolia, Switzerland and Democratic Congo from Sept. 27 to Oct. 2 on the occasion of the 61st founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 80th anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union.
 On display at the venues were photos showing the leadership exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il in party building and introducing the glorious history of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 N. Sarantuya, vice-chairman of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development, said in his speech at a meeting that the WPK which grew from the deep and strong roots of the DIU has laid firm foundations for prosperity of posterity, surmounting all hardships and ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Martin Lotscher, chairman of the Swiss Committee for Supporting the Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, addressing a meeting, introduced the victorious and glorious course of the WPK and called for more actively conducting solidarity movement supporting the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kanga Ngerien Jerom, chairman of the Group for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea of Democratic Congo, at a reading session on book "Short Biography of Kim Il Sung" laid stress on acquiring their undying exploits more deeply. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Mongolia and Switzerland.

S. Korean Security Authorities' Plot under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Jang Song Hoe, chairman of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon), reportedly released a statement titled "We strongly denounce the security authorities for plotting to fabricate a 'case of off-stage organizing Hanchongryon'" on October 2.
 The statement recalled that it was disclosed at the trial of Choe Hui Jong, permanent member of the "south Korean Civil Rights Institute", on September 26 that the security authorities made a surprise search of his house and detained him under a scenario for rigging up the "case of off-stage organizing Hanchongryon." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing indignation at the moves of the security authorities to fabricate the case, talking about the non-existent "forces wire-pulling Hanchongryon," the statement demanded the security authorities immediately stop their anachronistic plot. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The activities of Hanchongryon, an independent organization of students, are just, the statement said, urging the security authorities to withdraw the label of "enemy-benefiting organization" from Hanchongryon and legalize the organization.

Japan's Doctrine on "Building Pacifist State" Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- The Japanese ruling quarters are nowadays uttering that they have "built a peaceful and democratic country" while "honestly repenting" of the past.
 In this regard, Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their flippant remarks are nothing but a sophism to cover up the reactionary nature of Japan's politics and disguise itself as a "pacifist state".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whether Japan has so far opted for the path of peace or not can be fully proved by Japan's stand and attitude towards its past war crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet settled its past even 60 years after the Second World War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarists have viciously schemed to erase its past history of crimes forever. If Japan, a war criminal state, truly wants to take the road of peace, it is very important for it to probe its past crimes of aggression and educate the Japanese so as not to commit such crimes again. On the contrary, however, Japan negated, distorted or totally erased in history textbooks the facts on the Japanese imperialists' crimes of aggression on Korea and other Asian countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese ruling quarters have embellished the war criminals as "patriotic martyrs" and "heroes" and instigated the Japanese to advocate and follow the Japanese imperialists' history of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the Second World War, Japan has frantically sped up its military preparations for reinvasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan completely revised the military principles of its "Self-Defence Forces." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has restored the right to belligerency and the right to participate in a war and reduced the "pacifist constitution" to a mere name by enacting various laws on war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are now viciously bent on the moves to abolish the "pacifist constitution" itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a sheer lie to remark that Japan has tried to "build a pacifist state" while "honestly repenting" of its past, the article points out, branding Japan's doctrine on "building the pacifist state" as a doctrine on building a war state and an advertisement of militarist aggression.

Palestinian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- Mohammad Shahta Zarab, Palestinian ambassador to the DPRK, hosted a reception at the embassy on Saturday to celebrate the 61st anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The ambassador said in a speech at the reception that the foundation of the WPK by President Kim Il Sung helped the Korean people to bring about changes in hewing out their destiny and have a powerful political leadership guiding the revolution and construction to victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's policy of building a party of Juche has been successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il and the WPK has made steady progress in different fields by infusing the Korean people with the Juche idea and the Songun idea, the ambassador noted, and pointed out: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people and the leadership of Palestine will remain true to the comradely friendship and bonds with the WPK and the Korean people. They always remember the consistent support and encouragement immortal Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il extended to them even under the most difficult conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the WPK Central Committee, said in a speech that the foundation of the WPK by Kim Il Sung on October 10, 1945 was a solemn historic declaration heralding the birth of a revolutionary party of new type guided by the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it is led by Kim Jong Il, the WPK has come to greet the heyday of carrying forward the cause of Juche and is more brilliantly shining as a revolutionary party of Juche, the party of Kim Il Sung, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK and the Korean people extend full support and solidarity to the Palestinian people in their struggle to retake their lost territory and legitimate national rights, he said, stressing: The just cause of the Palestinian people is sure to win.

Rodong Sinmun on History of Kim Jong Il's Leadership over WPK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 8 (KCNA) -- The 40-odd-year history of Kim Jong Il's leadership over the Workers' Party of Korea is shining as the history of great creation in which he brought about overall prosperity of Korean-style socialism by organizationally and ideologically strengthening the party and enhancing its leadership roll with his outstanding wisdom and extraordinary political ability, the immortal annals in which he has led the cause of anti-imperialist independence in the present era to victory.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday editorially says this. It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his leadership over the party is also shining as an undying chronicle in which he has strengthened and developed the party into a seasoned guide of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has made great efforts to strengthen the party and the military power in order to lead the Korean revolution along the way of Songun paved by President Kim Il Sung.
 His outstanding far-sightedness and immortal leadership history are the basic secret that helped the party to lead the cause of Songun to a brilliant victory, always taking the initiative even under the complex situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his leadership over the party is the great history emerging victorious as ever in revolution and construction with the might of ideology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set a brilliant example in modeling the whole party on the great Juche idea, advancing the revolution with the might of ideology and opening the heyday of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his leadership over the party is a sacred history during which the single-minded unity of the party and revolutionary ranks has been cemented and the great miracles wrought by its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the immortal history of his leadership over the party building, the Korean army and people have come to have eternal treasure enough to accomplish the Juche cause of Songun to the end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should display the might of Songun Korea and bring about a great surge in the building a great prosperous powerful nation under the leadership of Kim Jong Il who is successfully accomplishing the cause of party building of Juche century after century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson stresses in an editorial that his leadership serves as a resources of the strength of the invincible WPK.

Important Days in DPRK Observed Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Lectures were given in Democratic Congo and Uganda and by the Pan-African Movement from September 25 to 28 on the occasion of the 61st anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 80th anniversary of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU).
 The deputy general secretary of the People's Rally for Socialism of Democratic Congo, in a lecture titled "The Workers' Party of Korea dynamically advancing along the road paved by the DIU" said that President Kim Il Sung formed the DIU, providing the historic roots of the WPK. The President founded the party before anything else after Korea's liberation and developed it into invincible militant ranks, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Justin Keyune, chief of the Group for the Study of Songun Politics of Kampala Coloro Higher Middle School of Uganda, in a lecture titled "The eternal party of President Kim Il Sung" highly praised the feats the President performed for building the party, stressing that the WPK would always demonstrate its might as the dignified party of the President as it is led by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deputy director of the Political Department of the Pan-African Movement, in a lecture titled "The reliable vanguard of the socialist cause" noted that the WPK is recognized by the international community as an invincible party, the most authoritative and dignified party for the feats it performed for the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence.

Proposal for Founding DFRK Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Phanindra Raj Pant, deputy secretary general of the Afro-Asian People's Solidarity Committee of Nepal and secretary of the Nepalese Committee for Promotion of Reunification of Korea, made public a statement on October 3 on the occasion of the 26th anniversary of the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo.
 The statement said that the proposal is the most realistic one to reunify Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that Kim Jong Il formulated the three principles of national reunification, the proposal for founding the DFRK and the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation as the three charters for national reunification and ushered in the June 15 era of reunification, thus performing immortal feats for the cause of Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement sincerely wished Kim Jong Il good health for the greater success of the Korean people in their struggle to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country at an early date, smash all sorts of the imperialists' moves and build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation.

S. Korean Judicial Authorities' Fascist Outrage Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Some time ago, the south Korean judicial authorities detained the persons who manufactured CDs on the Juche idea and posted on Internet homepage articles supporting the Songun politics, by invoking the notorious "National Security Law" (NSL).
 This was an outrageous fascist action intended to dampen the desire for national reconciliation and independent reunification daily growing among the south Korean people and check the rapid spread of the Juche idea and the tendency of supporting and praising the Songun politics, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea and the Songun politics are a just idea and patriotic politics as they indicate the way of realizing the popular masses' independence and protect the dignity, sovereignty and security of the nation, the news analyst says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the south Korean judicial authorities took the above-said action under the unreasonable pretext of introducing the idea and politics recognized by the world people and supported by all Koreans. This repression can never be justified. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their action fully reveals the true nature of "liberal democracy" and "human rights" advocated by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They charged the above-said persons with "pro-north activities" and "activities praising the north." How can they dare repeat the conception of confrontation dating back to the old era of fascist dictatorship. They are still invoking such outdated anti-reunification fascist law as NSL though national cooperation, reconciliation and the movement for independent reunification have become a trend of the times. This reckless deed can be perpetrated only by those devoid of elementary sense of the trend of the times and awareness of belonging to the same nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean judicial authorities are bound to be cursed and condemned by all the fellow countrymen for their unprecedented treacherous action going against the trend of the times and the nation's desire.

Songun Policy Favored by S. Korean Organizations
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Different organizations in south Korea including the Reunification Solidarity and the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions posted on their Internet homepages an article titled "We are determined to positively cover and report about the Songun policy" contributed by the Association of Media Persons Supporting the Songun Policy on September 30.
 The article said the United States has put the world in disorder with its high-handed policy based on unilateralism but dared not provoke the north, adding that the reason is that the north pursues the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the north has been fully prepared to meet the military pressure of the U.S., the article went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north has kept itself ready to stand in the confrontation with the U.S., pursuant to the Songun policy, its unique political mode of solving all the issues of the country by attaching utmost importance to military affairs and giving priority to the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north has already declared that it is fully prepared to respond to a war with a war and to a dialogue with a dialogue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north in which the whole society is single-mindedly united has stepped up the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, thinking about its future rather than the stand-off with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We would like to clarify that from now on we would cover in detail how the north struggles against the U.S., pursuant to its Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article said that their news coverage would help record the decisive driving force for achieving peace and reunification of the Korean Peninsula in history.

Kim Jong Suk Honored in Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk was awarded the title of chief of tribe "Great Mother of All" and a commemorative key of Aba City of Nigeria on the occasion of the significant holidays in October.
 An awarding ceremony was held by the Ohazu Egbelu Autonomous Community in Aba city in Abia State of Nigeria as a traditional function of the community on September 23. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the great king, several kings, tribal chiefs, members of the council of kings and others. Staff members of the DPRK embassy and Korean technicians in Nigeria were among those present on invitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There was a briefing on the revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Suk. Then the great king conveyed to an official of the embassy a certificate of the above-said title of the tribal chief, the decorative articles to go with the chief and the commemorative key proving the honorary citizenship of Aba City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great king said that the community has the honor of awarding the title of chief of tribe "Great Mother of All" and commemorative key of Aba City to Kim Jong Suk on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK, the 61st anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea and the 80th anniversary of the Down-with-Imperialism Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The community's conferment of the honorary title upon Kim Jong Suk, the first foreigner ever to receive it, was aimed to highly praise the great feats performed by her for the era and humankind, he said, adding this was great honor and pride for the community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter of the great king to Kim Jong Il was read out at the ceremony.

KCNA Flails Japan's Bid to Host 2016 Olympics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- Japan is working hard to host 2016 Olympics.
  It is busy with diplomacy to garner support and sympathy from the international community, while making eyes at the IOC. It is also keen to give impression that Japan can host Olympics. This is enough to make a cat laugh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is the only country that has not yet shaken off its ill-fame of an enemy state in the political field. It is a country having bubble economy as it has nothing indigenous. As far as security is concerned, this country is plagued with hooliganism. This being a hard reality, Japan is so keen on the sponsorship of the Olympics. This only indicates that politicians and those concerned with sports in this country know little where it stands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is not in a position to host Olympics. It is branded as a "Pandora's box" and has not yet been recognized as an "ordinary and normal state" by the world people as it has not yet redeemed its past but worked hard to revive militarism and committed such crimes as luring and abduction operations and human rights abuses at home in the new century, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japanese politicians do not stoop to any infamy to attain their political purposes, just as their country does. They are political dwarfs and dregs in the sports circle as they behave in breach of even the pure sports spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is clearly proved by the fact that Japan prevented DPRK players from participating in the 2006 Synchronized Swimming World Cup and the 15th East Asia Junior Table-Tennis Championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that the Japanese reactionaries will put pressure upon those countries which incur their displeasure and prevent them from participating in the Olympic games at the instruction of their masters, the stereotyped method whereby they refused to issue visas to the DPRK players and completely blocked their entry, citing a certain "clause" as a pretext for the refusal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan instigated the organizing committee of the East Asia Junior Table-Tennis Championships to send to the DPRK a notice requesting the DPRK side to refrain from sending its players due to the concern about their safety under the prevailing situation.
 How can Japan be called a "law-governed state" when it says it can hardly guarantee the safety of those participants in the junior championships from a few East Asian countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan keeps its economy going through plunder of other countries and overseas expansion and increased dependence on big powers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such country instable in political, economic, security and all other aspects makes a strong bid for hosting Olympiad, unaware of its real position. This cannot but be a height of folly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Explicitly speaking, the Japanese reactionaries' bid to make Olympics their political plaything is nothing but a serious insult to the sacred Olympic Charter and its idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Olympic Charter stipulates that the Olympics shall contribute to improving people's health, enhancing their noble morality and promoting international friendship and thus preserving world peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan will invite international isolation if it makes a bid for hosting Olympics without a proper view and attitude toward international sports games.

S. Korean Authorities' Crackdown on "NGEU" Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea Saturday made public a statement denouncing the south Korean authorities' crackdown on the "National Government Employees' Union" (NGEU) as an unpardonable anti-democratic, anti-national crime.
 The south Korean authorities recently sent the police to close office rooms of the "NGEU" and detain more than 60 hard core members of the union, charging that it is an illegal organization which is doing "illegal actions" demanding a halt to the south Korea-U.S. joint military exercises and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities' suppression of the union is an undisguised move to stamp out the progressive movement organization and a wanton infringement upon human rights, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The demand of "NGEU" for ensuring the three rights of labor and a stop to the south Korea-U.S. joint military exercises can neither be called in question nor be an object of suppression as it is a very righteous struggle to achieve democratic rights and freedom and defend national dignity and sovereignty from the outside forces' aggression and interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should squarely see the aspiration of the people and the trend of the times, immediately stop the suppression of the union and immediately release those unionists detained without condition.

"Reorganization" of U.S. Forces in S. Korea Condemned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 7 (KCNA) -- The ongoing "reorganization" of the U.S. forces in south Korea is part of the arms buildup and a prelude to a war of aggression against the DPRK. A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland declared this in a statement Saturday.
 The "reduction" and "reorganization" of troops in south Korea being carried out by the United States are prompted by its sinister design to accelerate arms buildup and war preparations in the Korean Peninsula by reorganizing the forces into a task force and use south Korea as a shock force in carrying out a new war, the statement pointed out, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Due to such moves the situation is getting tenser and the danger of a nuclear war is further increasing on the Korean Peninsula as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is the fact that the bellicose forces in south Korea are stepping up the arms buildup and north-targeted war preparations, while openly asserting these are meant to strike it, pursuant to the U.S. scenario for a war against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an intolerable crime against the nation as it breaches the June 15 joint declaration and drives the inter-Korean relations to a phase of catastrophe and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean war-like forces are bound to face punishment by the nation and self-destruction as they are hell-bent on the war moves bringing the nation to ruin, serving the U.S. in its moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should pull its aggression forces out of south Korea and its vicinity at once.
